Python Comments

- Single-line: everything after # on that line is ignored by Python.
- Multi-line strings with triple quotes """ ... """ can be used as a docstring at the top of a file or function; if not assigned, they act like a string literal (often used for temporary comment blocks—prefer # for short notes).

Comments explain intent for humans; they do not change how the program runs.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_comments.asp

